Question 1:
Euclidian distance : 
Q&A = sqroot(((2-1)**2)+((1-1)**2))=1
Q&B = sqroot(((2-2)**2)+((1-2)**2))=1
Q&C = sqroot(((2-4)**2)+((1-4)**2))= 3.61
The two closest point to Q are A(cat)&B(dog) , it’s a tie , because of situation like this when using knn classification we use an odd number for the hyperparameter 'K'
for example if we used k=3 the answer would be dog

