Question 4:
p1(0,1),p2(1,3),p3((2,5),p4((3,9)
p1error= y==1 = 2(0) + 1=1   y'1'=1       1-1 =0 
p2error=y==3=2(1) +1   3=2+1  3=3   3-3 = 0
p3error=y==5=2(2)+1  5=4+1  5=5       5-5=0 
p4error=y==9=2(3)+1  9=6+1   9=7   9-7=2

MSE = ((p1**2)+ (p2**2)+ (p3**2)+ (p4**2))/4
=(0+0+0+4)/4=1
MSE=1

sse= 0+0+0+2 sqrd =4
yˉ=(1+3+5+9)/4=18/4=4.5

sst=(4.5-1)**2+(4.5-3)**2+(4.5-5)**2+(4.5-9)**2
sst= 12.25+2.25+0.25+20.25=35

R²= 1- 4.5/35=0.871
n=4
p=1

Adjusted R² = 1-((1- 0.871)*(4-1)/(4-1-1))
Adjusted R² = 1 - (0.129 * 3 / 2)
Adjusted R² = 0.8065

--------------------------------------------------

Question 5:
Aginiimpurty=LEFT((0) BOTH SUCSESS ) RIGHT (2S 4F)
Gini(right) = 1 − ((1/3)² + (2/3)²) = 0.444
Weighted gini = 0.444*6/8+0*2/8 = 0.333
Gini gain A = 0.5 – 0.333= 0.167 

Bginiimpurty=LEFT(3 SUCSESS (0)) RIGHT (1S 4F)
Gini(right) = 1 − ((1/5)² + (4/5)²) = 0.32
Weighted gini = 0.32*5/8+0*3/8 = 0.2
Gini gain B = 0.5 – 0.2= 0.3 

Cginiimpurty=LEFT(3 SUCSESS 1F) RIGHT (1S 4F)
Gini(left) = 1 − ((1/4)² + (3/4)²) = 0.375 
Gini(right) = 1 − ((1/4)² + (3/4)²) = 0.375
Weighted gini = 0.375*4/8+0.375*4/8 = 0.375
Gini gain C = 0.5 – 0.375 = 0.125

Dginiimpurty=LEFT(1 SUCSESS 1F 0.5) RIGHT (3S 3F 0.5)
No gain

Final answer B has the biggest gini gain with 0.3

